01:01:25,237 --> 01:01:26,764
that's really connected
with the radiation.

774
01:01:30,453 --> 01:01:32,657
What about
that contaminated truck?

775
01:01:32,694 --> 01:01:35,345
They cut up this hot truck
and buried it.

776
01:01:35,381 --> 01:01:37,007
Right.
That was in your letter.

777
01:01:37,045 --> 01:01:39,729
I've got to catch my plane.
Paul will take care of you.

778
01:01:39,766 --> 01:01:41,589
The only way
we can get enough votes...

779
01:01:41,622 --> 01:01:43,444
to keep the union
in your plant...

780
01:01:43,478 --> 01:01:45,867
is on the health
and safety issue.

781
01:01:45,910 --> 01:01:49,107
So we'll get a couple of
hotshot doctors in to speak.

782
01:01:49,142 --> 01:01:51,248
You keep telling
Paul all this stuff.

783
01:01:51,287 --> 01:01:53,654
And try to get
everything clear...

784
01:01:53,687 --> 01:01:56,207
for the AEC tomorrow,
all right?

785
01:01:56,246 --> 01:01:59,378
I'll be back in a second.

786
01:01:59,415 --> 01:02:00,844
Max?

787
01:02:03,416 --> 01:02:06,285
I'm going to go find
a restroom.

788
01:02:13,126 --> 01:02:16,258
Excuse me.
There's one more thing.

789
01:02:16,294 --> 01:02:18,846
I work in metallography.
In X-rays.

790
01:02:18,886 --> 01:02:22,748
And sometimes we...

791
01:02:22,789 --> 01:02:26,084
Quite frankly,
we have negatives altered.

792
01:02:28,902 --> 01:02:31,803
The negatives of the welds
in the fuel rods.

793
01:02:31,845 --> 01:02:36,101
They take a weld
and cross section it.

794
01:02:36,133 --> 01:02:39,231
Then they photograph it,
and there's a defect.

795
01:02:39,268 --> 01:02:42,946
Then they just touch it up.

796
01:02:42,981 --> 01:02:44,868
Touch it up?

797
01:02:44,900 --> 01:02:49,178
With a Pentel pen.
Right on the negatives.

798
01:02:49,220 --> 01:02:50,562
They fill in the white spots.

799
01:02:50,596 --> 01:02:52,800
You're talking about
X- rays of fuel rods?

800
01:02:52,837 --> 01:02:55,585
The fuel rods
they're sending up to that...

801
01:02:55,620 --> 01:02:58,817
We're sending up to
that breeder reactor...

802
01:02:58,852 --> 01:03:01,438
they're testing in Hanford.

803
01:03:01,476 --> 01:03:04,323
Do you know what that means?

804
01:03:04,355 --> 01:03:06,657
I know they shouldn't do it.

805
01:03:06,691 --> 01:03:08,633
Excuse us.

806
01:03:08,675 --> 01:03:11,545
Why don't we go in there?

807
01:03:14,595 --> 01:03:16,253
In an ordinary nuclear plant...

808
01:03:16,290 --> 01:03:18,560
you can have meltdowns,
poisonous gas, and dead people.

809
01:03:18,595 --> 01:03:22,391
That's nothing compared to what
can go wrong with a breeder.

810
01:03:22,434 --> 01:03:26,297
You put defective fuel rods
in a breeder reactor...

811
01:03:26,339 --> 01:03:30,201
for all we know, the whole
state could be wiped out.

812
01:03:30,242 --> 01:03:32,413
Can you get
documentation of that?

813
01:03:35,586 --> 01:03:37,113
I guess so.

814
01:03:37,154 --> 01:03:40,666
If you could get documentation,
that would be very important.

815
01:03:40,705 --> 01:03:43,705
We'll set you up with a reporter
from the "New York Times"...

816
01:03:43,745 --> 01:03:46,614
get the company up against
the wall on negotiations.

817
01:03:46,656 --> 01:03:49,079
But you'd have to have
documentation.

818
01:03:49,122 --> 01:03:51,838
I don't know about putting
names in the newspaper.

819
01:03:51,873 --> 01:03:53,083
Names aren't the point.

820
01:03:53,121 --> 01:03:55,455
The point is
that if you're right...

821
01:03:55,489 --> 01:03:57,179
they could kill off
two million people.

822
01:03:57,216 --> 01:04:01,723
There's a moral imperative
involved here.

823
01:04:06,049 --> 01:04:09,496
Think about it.
Talk to Paul.

824
01:04:09,536 --> 01:04:11,511
You look like a standup girl.

825
01:04:11,552 --> 01:04:13,178
I'll be right there.

826
01:04:28,543 --> 01:04:32,187
I've never seen
so many bands in my life.

827
01:04:49,310 --> 01:04:52,059
All right,
we're going to go over...

828
01:04:52,093 --> 01:04:53,654
your statements
for the AEC meeting.

829
01:04:53,694 --> 01:04:56,825
And later, you and I
will go through yours.

830
01:05:01,694 --> 01:05:04,726
There was 23 people there,
including us.

831
01:05:04,765 --> 01:05:05,877
Of course, I couldn't
take any pictures...

832
01:05:05,918 --> 01:05:07,706
while the meeting
was going on.

833
01:05:07,742 --> 01:05:10,108
Just imagine
all these old geezers...

834
01:05:10,141 --> 01:05:12,029
sitting there,
pitchers of water...

835
01:05:12,062 --> 01:05:13,686
and they all looked so bored.

836
01:05:13,725 --> 01:05:16,278
It's like they had
heard it all before.

837
01:05:16,317 --> 01:05:20,114
I think the union's
really going to help us now.

838
01:05:21,629 --> 01:05:22,970
That doesn't
belong in here at all.

839
01:05:23,004 --> 01:05:27,445
That's one of them slides
you can buy.

840
01:05:27,485 --> 01:05:30,300
Oh, hell. May, did you
put them in this order?

841
01:05:30,332 --> 01:05:33,299
I didn't touch them, Quincy.

842
01:05:33,340 --> 01:05:37,115
There's the Lincoln Memorial,
of course.

843
01:05:37,148 --> 01:05:38,903
That's where we stayed.

844
01:05:38,939 --> 01:05:40,979
I couldn't get it
all in the picture.

845
01:05:43,163 --> 01:05:45,618
You could get dinner
in your room if you wanted...

846
01:05:45,660 --> 01:05:48,147
but we didn't.

847
01:05:50,555 --> 01:05:52,922
I had one of the waiters
take this one.

848
01:05:52,955 --> 01:05:55,476
Who's that guy?

849
01:05:55,515 --> 01:05:58,035
That's Paul Stone.
He works for the union.

850
01:05:59,675 --> 01:06:03,253
This is on the way
to the airport.

851
01:06:03,291 --> 01:06:05,145
And that's the White House.

852
01:06:05,178 --> 01:06:07,154
I wanted to take a picture
of ol' Gerry Ford...

853
01:06:07,195 --> 01:06:10,675
cooking his English muffin,
but they wouldn't let us in.

854
01:06:21,913 --> 01:06:24,214
How many people know about
you going to Washington?

855
01:06:24,249 --> 01:06:27,565
Only the people in that room.

856
01:06:27,609 --> 01:06:30,326
Quincy and Morgan
know about your spying?

857
01:06:32,633 --> 01:06:33,909
No.

858
01:06:38,073 --> 01:06:40,342
People are going
to lose jobs, Karen.

859
01:06:40,377 --> 01:06:43,312
Some of them ought to.

860
01:06:43,353 --> 01:06:45,686
There's a moral imperative here.

861
01:06:49,785 --> 01:06:52,784
You going to put
some big story in the papers?

862
01:06:52,824 --> 01:06:53,906
In the "New York Times."

863
01:06:54,040 --> 01:06:57,040
In the "New York Times."

864
01:07:00,279 --> 01:07:03,029
Guess that about ties
the package up with a bow.

865
01:07:41,430 --> 01:07:43,284
What's the matter with him?

866
01:07:44,854 --> 01:07:47,820
Some guy in Washington
I should have told him about.

867
01:07:47,861 --> 01:07:51,690
- Is that all?
- No.

868
01:08:10,900 --> 01:08:12,590
What you doing?

869
01:08:14,421 --> 01:08:15,849
Thinking.

870
01:08:25,939 --> 01:08:28,657
Thinking. Drinking.

871
01:08:33,139 --> 01:08:34,382
I was just thinking...

872
01:08:34,419 --> 01:08:36,906
if you'd ever quit
and come away with me.

873
01:08:42,194 --> 01:08:45,194
Well, I can't quit now.

874
01:08:45,235 --> 01:08:48,550
That's what I was thinking.

875
01:08:59,473 --> 01:09:01,677
It's cold out here.

876
01:09:01,714 --> 01:09:04,365
Come on inside.

877
01:09:04,401 --> 01:09:05,863
I quit.

878
01:09:10,833 --> 01:09:12,720
You what?

879
01:09:12,753 --> 01:09:15,120
This afternoon.
Gave my notice.

880
01:09:15,153 --> 01:09:17,542
- You quit?
- That's what I said.

881
01:09:21,873 --> 01:09:23,782
This afternoon?

882
01:09:26,673 --> 01:09:28,745
Why didn't you tell me?

883
01:09:31,951 --> 01:09:34,123
I don't know.
I just didn't tell you.

884
01:09:40,048 --> 01:09:42,436
Why'd you quit?

885
01:09:45,328 --> 01:09:48,676
I just don't give a shit.

886
01:09:58,287 --> 01:10:00,708
You don't give a shit
if everybody in the plant...

887
01:10:00,750 --> 01:10:02,855
is being poisoned?

888
01:10:24,878 --> 01:10:28,074
Don't give me a problem
I can't solve.

889
01:11:12,395 --> 01:11:14,282
Did you take
the Waylon Jennings tapes?

890
01:11:14,314 --> 01:11:16,203
I left them for you.

891
01:11:16,235 --> 01:11:18,885
They're yours.
You can take them.

892
01:11:20,554 --> 01:11:22,922
You can keep them, Karen.

893
01:11:29,194 --> 01:11:30,820
Take it easy, Dolly.

894
01:12:01,256 --> 01:12:03,973
Drew, come on. Stay.

895
01:12:05,769 --> 01:12:09,029
Sweetheart, it's like
you're two people.

896
01:12:09,063 --> 01:12:10,853
I'm in love
with one of them...

897
01:12:10,888 --> 01:12:12,578
but the other one's...

898
01:12:12,615 --> 01:12:15,876
Just a general pain in the ass.

899
01:12:54,342 --> 01:12:56,446
I loved it, baby.

900
01:14:05,922 --> 01:14:07,351
What are you doing in there?

901
01:14:15,457 --> 01:14:18,905
What are you doing in my desk?

902
01:14:18,945 --> 01:14:22,392
If I tell you, you'll promise
not to tell anybody?

903
01:14:25,633 --> 01:14:28,567
I keep my pills in there,
in that drawer...

904
01:14:28,608 --> 01:14:31,325
because I have an allergy...

905
01:14:31,361 --> 01:14:34,459
and they don't let you bring
medication into the plant...

906
01:14:34,496 --> 01:14:36,602
so I hid them in there.

907
01:14:38,336 --> 01:14:40,572
I don't believe you.

908
01:14:42,081 --> 01:14:46,422
I think you should take
a person's word for something.

909
01:15:15,327 --> 01:15:18,174
These don't look like
antihistamines to me.

910
01:15:19,615 --> 01:15:23,094
Winston,
you know what these are?

911
01:15:23,134 --> 01:15:27,607
These are little
tiny time capsules...

912
01:15:27,646 --> 01:15:31,540
like the ones you see on TV.

913
01:15:31,581 --> 01:15:33,654
They clear up
your nasal passages...

914
01:15:33,693 --> 01:15:37,010
for up to 12 hours straight.

915
01:15:43,645 --> 01:15:46,546
- Excuse me.
- God bless you.

916
01:15:48,478 --> 01:15:50,932
In the coal mines years ago...

917
01:15:50,972 --> 01:15:54,715
they used to put canaries
in the tunnels.

918
01:15:54,749 --> 01:15:56,952
If the canaries dropped dead...

919
01:15:56,988 --> 01:15:58,963
they knew there was a gas leak.

920
01:16:01,052 --> 01:16:03,867
But it's a brand-new industry...

921
01:16:03,900 --> 01:16:06,583
so you're the canaries.

922
01:16:06,621 --> 01:16:09,654
The trouble is, you're not going
to drop dead right away.

923
01:16:09,692 --> 01:16:12,593
It might take ten years.
Twenty. We don't know.

924
01:16:12,635 --> 01:16:19,705
Here's what we know...
plutonium causes cancer.

925
01:16:19,739 --> 01:16:21,146
Anybody tells you
we don't know...

926
01:16:21,179 --> 01:16:24,080
how much plutonium
causes cancer, they're lying.

927
01:16:24,122 --> 01:16:25,912
What we don't know...

928
01:16:25,948 --> 01:16:30,223
is how little plutonium
causes cancer.

929
01:16:30,266 --> 01:16:31,794
The government says...

930
01:16:31,835 --> 01:16:34,452
that the maximum
permissible body burden...

931
01:16:34,490 --> 01:16:37,240
for your lifetime
is 40 nanocuries.

932
01:16:37,274 --> 01:16:39,031
Let me tell you
how much that is.

933
01:16:39,066 --> 01:16:44,303
That is a tiny dot
on a piece of paper.

934
01:16:44,346 --> 01:16:49,300
We say that's too much.

935
01:16:49,338 --> 01:16:55,382
We say that it takes
less than that to kill you.

936
01:16:55,418 --> 01:16:58,036
We don't say
it's twice too much...

937
01:16:58,073 --> 01:16:59,960
or three times too much.

938
01:16:59,993 --> 01:17:06,637
We think that that is
115,000 times too much.

939
01:17:07,993 --> 01:17:11,921
A pollen-sized
grain of plutonium...

940
01:17:11,960 --> 01:17:15,256
injected in mice
causes cancer.

941
01:17:15,288 --> 01:17:20,242
When you inhale it,
and it lodges in your lungs...

942
01:17:20,281 --> 01:17:23,696
you're married to cancer.

943
01:17:23,736 --> 01:17:26,486
We've been through
all the training literature...

944
01:17:26,520 --> 01:17:29,519
Kerr McGee hands out
to new employees...

945
01:17:29,559 --> 01:17:32,876
and there's nothing
about cancer.

946
01:17:32,919 --> 01:17:39,312
Did management give you
any literature about cancer?

947
01:17:39,351 --> 01:17:42,384
Then you get contaminated,
and they tell you...

948
01:17:42,422 --> 01:17:44,245
you've had an acceptable level
of contamination.

949
01:17:44,280 --> 01:17:47,475
I say there's no such thing.

950
01:17:49,558 --> 01:17:51,533
There must be some questions.

951
01:17:57,366 --> 01:18:01,522
Is there any way to get
the plutonium out of you...

952
01:18:01,558 --> 01:18:05,649
if it's inside your lungs?

953
01:18:05,686 --> 01:18:10,421
You can take the lung out,
but that's a little extreme.

954
01:18:20,342 --> 01:18:22,196
You want to get
something to eat?

955
01:18:22,229 --> 01:18:24,235
Very nice meeting you.

956
01:18:24,277 --> 01:18:26,099
Have a good night.

957
01:18:26,133 --> 01:18:28,173
That was great.

958
01:18:28,213 --> 01:18:30,546
The union is really in solid.

959
01:18:30,580 --> 01:18:32,468
We don't have to worry about...

960
01:18:32,501 --> 01:18:35,184
How come why didn't we hear
any of this before?

961
01:18:35,220 --> 01:18:36,910
And we didn't see
any of you guys...

962
01:18:36,947 --> 01:18:42,382
until they decided
to vote the union out or not?

963
01:18:42,420 --> 01:18:43,532
If you're
so worried about us...

964
01:18:43,572 --> 01:18:44,816
where the hell were you
in the beginning?

965
01:18:44,852 --> 01:18:47,121
What we're saying
is you need someone...

966
01:18:47,156 --> 01:18:48,781
Iooking out for
your health and safety.

967
01:18:48,819 --> 01:18:50,543
The company says
they're taking care of you.

968
01:18:50,580 --> 01:18:51,724
Do you believe that?

969
01:18:51,763 --> 01:18:53,771
- Yeah. I believe that.
- You do?

970
01:18:53,811 --> 01:18:55,752
You're the only guy
in that room that still does.

971
01:18:55,794 --> 01:18:57,650
Let me tell you something else.

972
01:18:57,684 --> 01:19:00,017
Doesn't matter if you work
on plutonium or dog food...

973
01:19:00,051 --> 01:19:01,611
because
they won't give you a thing.

974
01:19:01,651 --> 01:19:04,750
There's nowhere left to go.
You start causing problems...

975
01:19:04,787 --> 01:19:08,562
and Kerr McGee shuts
that plant down, then what?

976
01:19:08,595 --> 01:19:11,628
You're up in Washington, D.C.

977
01:19:11,666 --> 01:19:15,049
We're down here out of work.

978
01:19:15,090 --> 01:19:17,992
Your cancer is a maybe.
That's all it is.

979
01:19:25,969 --> 01:19:28,359
- He's just scared.
- Yeah.

980
01:19:28,402 --> 01:19:29,995
The meeting was really good.

981
01:19:30,033 --> 01:19:34,768
Yeah, look...
I got an early plane, Karen.

982
01:19:34,802 --> 01:19:36,808
Meaning what?

983
01:19:36,849 --> 01:19:40,941
I don't think this is smart,
us getting involved.

984
01:19:40,977 --> 01:19:43,497
We already got involved.

985
01:20:11,024 --> 01:20:13,576
Hi. This is Paul Stone.

986
01:20:13,615 --> 01:20:14,728
I'm out right now...

987
01:20:14,767 --> 01:20:17,102
but if you leave
a message after the beep...

988
01:20:17,135 --> 01:20:19,884
I'll get back to you.

989
01:20:19,918 --> 01:20:22,341
Hi, this is Karen.

990
01:20:25,102 --> 01:20:27,688
I just wanted
to let you know...

991
01:20:27,727 --> 01:20:31,818
that we won
the union election 80 to 61...

992
01:20:31,854 --> 01:20:34,888
and I'm real happy.

993
01:20:38,349 --> 01:20:40,260
It's real hard
to keep calling you...

994
01:20:40,303 --> 01:20:42,026
from a pay phone
if you're never there...

995
01:20:42,062 --> 01:20:46,437
so that's why
I'm calling you from here.

996
01:20:48,045 --> 01:20:51,340
I have some things that...

997
01:20:51,374 --> 01:20:52,803
I really need
to talk to you about...

998
01:20:52,845 --> 01:20:55,495
and I just wish
that I could talk to you.

999
01:20:55,532 --> 01:20:59,908
Been under a lot
of pressure here, boy.

1000
01:20:59,949 --> 01:21:02,370
It's great
we won and everything...

1001
01:21:02,412 --> 01:21:05,675
but just...

1002
01:21:05,709 --> 01:21:09,353
Been under really
a lot of pressure, and...

1003
01:21:09,389 --> 01:21:11,658
I don't know.
I feel like I'm...

1004
01:21:16,845 --> 01:21:19,145
All alone.

1005
01:21:23,212 --> 01:21:26,059
Guess you didn't hear
that last part.

1006
01:21:41,292 --> 01:21:43,746
Come on!

1007
01:21:47,210 --> 01:21:48,803
Do you want coffee?

1008
01:22:09,641 --> 01:22:10,819
I went to make popcorn
last night...

1009
01:22:10,858 --> 01:22:12,450
and there's no Wesson oil.

1010
01:22:12,489 --> 01:22:14,594
So, go get some.

1011
01:22:14,634 --> 01:22:16,160
I'm not in charge
of the Wesson oil...

1012
01:22:16,201 --> 01:22:17,795
I'm not in charge
of the shopping.

1013
01:22:17,833 --> 01:22:19,872
I can't do it every time.

1014
01:22:19,913 --> 01:22:23,142
I can't do it this afternoon.
I got a union meeting.

1015
01:22:23,176 --> 01:22:24,605
If you're
talking like that...

1016
01:22:24,649 --> 01:22:26,306
to impress that
outside agitator of yours...

1017
01:22:26,344 --> 01:22:27,773
he ain't here,
so cut the shit.

1018
01:22:27,816 --> 01:22:30,751
We can't do the shopping
unless you give us your key.

1019
01:22:34,280 --> 01:22:35,742
What happened to your key?

1020
01:22:35,785 --> 01:22:38,118
If we knew that,
we wouldn't need yours.

1021
01:22:38,152 --> 01:22:42,014
- I lost it.
- You lost it.

1022
01:22:44,423 --> 01:22:46,016
Leave it under the step.

1023
01:22:46,056 --> 01:22:48,870
What if somebody rapes me
