01:45:13,381 --> 01:45:15,518
Get out of my way!

1277
01:45:19,747 --> 01:45:23,772
Oh, Jesus!
Where am I going to go now?

1278
01:45:23,811 --> 01:45:26,145
I don't have anyplace to go now.

1279
01:45:26,179 --> 01:45:29,440
We're getting a room for Dolly.
We want to help you.

1280
01:45:29,474 --> 01:45:31,417
We can help you
with a place to stay.

1281
01:45:31,459 --> 01:45:33,052
We can help you with money.

1282
01:45:44,834 --> 01:45:48,763
But first I have
to sign something, right?

1283
01:45:48,802 --> 01:45:53,340
You want me to sign a statement
saying I did all this.

1284
01:45:53,378 --> 01:45:56,345
Just in your own words
what happened.

1285
01:46:02,753 --> 01:46:04,508
OK.

1286
01:46:12,191 --> 01:46:14,778
In my own words?

1287
01:46:16,832 --> 01:46:18,742
I'm contaminated.

1288
01:46:20,480 --> 01:46:22,389
I'm dying.

1289
01:49:06,647 --> 01:49:08,721
What are you doing here?

1290
01:49:08,760 --> 01:49:12,884
I'm just looking around,
like you.

1291
01:50:17,364 --> 01:50:19,306
You're here.

1292
01:50:19,348 --> 01:50:22,578
Jesus Christ.
I didn't know where you were.

1293
01:50:24,532 --> 01:50:26,538
What the hell happened?

1294
01:50:31,603 --> 01:50:33,425
They're killing me.

1295
01:50:33,459 --> 01:50:34,768
They're trying to kill me.

1296
01:50:34,804 --> 01:50:37,672
They want me
to stop what I'm doing.

1297
01:50:37,714 --> 01:50:41,260
They contaminated me,
you know that?

1298
01:50:41,299 --> 01:50:43,819
I'm internally contaminated now.

1299
01:50:45,586 --> 01:50:47,692
Now, you listen to me.

1300
01:50:47,731 --> 01:50:50,600
We're going to go
to Los Alamos on Thursday...

1301
01:50:50,642 --> 01:50:52,529
and we'll get a full body count
from some doctors...

1302
01:50:52,562 --> 01:50:54,220
who know what they're doing.
All three of us.

1303
01:50:54,259 --> 01:50:57,837
Oh, God! I'm so scared now.

1304
01:51:19,409 --> 01:51:22,126
It says here that
there's plutonium missing...

1305
01:51:22,161 --> 01:51:25,455
from just about every
nuclear plant in this country.

1306
01:51:25,488 --> 01:51:28,619
- Who's got it?
- Any asshole that wants it.

1307
01:51:28,657 --> 01:51:30,729
Man.

1308
01:51:30,769 --> 01:51:34,663
That's the guy, Drew.

1309
01:51:34,705 --> 01:51:36,427
The guy
Paul is bringing to see me.

1310
01:51:36,464 --> 01:51:37,893
Who?

1311
01:51:37,936 --> 01:51:40,238
The guy that wrote it,
from the "New York Times."

1312
01:51:40,272 --> 01:51:41,865
If you're going to be
in the newspaper...

1313
01:51:41,905 --> 01:51:44,108
I want to be in there, too.

1314
01:51:50,991 --> 01:51:54,340
Dolly, did you...

1315
01:51:54,383 --> 01:51:58,639
Did you tell the company
about the "New York Times"?

1316
01:51:58,671 --> 01:52:00,744
No. I don't think
I remembered that part.

1317
01:52:08,142 --> 01:52:10,598
Did you tell them
about the X-rays?

1318
01:52:13,550 --> 01:52:16,616
- Dolly?
- No.

1319
01:52:16,654 --> 01:52:18,694
Are you sure?

1320
01:52:18,735 --> 01:52:22,083
Karen, they know
everything about us.

1321
01:52:30,637 --> 01:52:33,223
They don't know
about the X-rays, do they?

1322
01:53:10,251 --> 01:53:12,969
OK. That's it.

1323
01:53:40,201 --> 01:53:43,616
All right, Mr. Stephens
and Miss Pelliker...

1324
01:53:43,658 --> 01:53:47,619
you both check out well below
permissible body limits.

1325
01:53:47,658 --> 01:53:50,210
You were exposed to
Miss Silkwood and the house...

1326
01:53:50,249 --> 01:53:53,991
but you show minimum
detectable activity now.

1327
01:53:56,265 --> 01:53:58,501
Miss Silkwood.

1328
01:54:02,153 --> 01:54:06,179
We have detected
americium in both lungs...

1329
01:54:06,217 --> 01:54:07,940
and both sides of your chest.

1330
01:54:07,976 --> 01:54:11,237
Americium is produced
when plutonium disintegrates.

1331
01:54:11,272 --> 01:54:13,792
And extrapolating from
your americium level...

1332
01:54:13,833 --> 01:54:16,614
we estimate you have
an internal contamination...

1333
01:54:16,648 --> 01:54:19,964
of six nanocuries of plutonium.

1334
01:54:20,007 --> 01:54:22,211
The maximum permissible
body burden...

1335
01:54:22,248 --> 01:54:25,696
for occupational exposure
is 40 nanocuries.

1336
01:54:25,736 --> 01:54:28,932
As you can see,
you are well under that level.

1337
01:54:28,967 --> 01:54:33,723
- I'm under it.
- As well as we can determine.

1338
01:54:33,766 --> 01:54:36,866
These are very sophisticated
instruments...

1339
01:54:36,904 --> 01:54:39,488
but their accuracy may be off...

1340
01:54:39,527 --> 01:54:42,658
by plus or minus 300%
at this level.

1341
01:54:44,167 --> 01:54:46,108
Plus or minus 300%?

1342
01:54:46,150 --> 01:54:47,645
That's correct.

1343
01:54:47,686 --> 01:54:49,890
Then what you're saying is...

1344
01:54:49,926 --> 01:54:51,933
that the amount
of plutonium inside me...

1345
01:54:51,974 --> 01:54:55,074
could be three times less
than you even think?

1346
01:54:55,111 --> 01:54:57,761
Or three times greater.

1347
01:54:59,525 --> 01:55:04,195
But even that would be under
the maximum body burden.

1348
01:55:16,517 --> 01:55:20,063
I think you should come on
down to Oklahoma City...

1349
01:55:20,101 --> 01:55:22,522
and bring that reporter
from the "New York Times."

1350
01:55:22,564 --> 01:55:25,499
Are you ready to see him?

1351
01:55:25,540 --> 01:55:26,947
I'm ready.

1352
01:55:26,981 --> 01:55:28,922
You got the documents?

1353
01:55:30,661 --> 01:55:32,034
Come on down.

1354
01:55:36,451 --> 01:55:41,023
Man, I love it here.
I love this country.

1355
01:55:41,059 --> 01:55:43,580
Wouldn't you like
to stay here forever?

1356
01:55:46,563 --> 01:55:49,051
Doctors are all goddamn liars.

1357
01:55:52,163 --> 01:55:55,294
Land's cheap there.

1358
01:55:55,332 --> 01:55:57,698
I read about this.

1359
01:55:57,730 --> 01:55:59,770
You can build yourself
a pueblo house.

1360
01:56:00,835 --> 01:56:04,218
Make it out of adobe brick,
like the Indians.

1361
01:56:04,259 --> 01:56:09,179
Mud, straw...
comes right out of the ground.

1362
01:56:09,218 --> 01:56:12,120
Got to build a well,
but that's not too bad.

1363
01:56:12,161 --> 01:56:14,617
You get a bunch of guys
to do you a favor.

1364
01:56:14,658 --> 01:56:15,967
You do them a favor.

1365
01:56:16,001 --> 01:56:18,489
It's all barter system
out there.

1366
01:56:18,529 --> 01:56:20,318
You can make the rooms
any shape.

1367
01:56:20,353 --> 01:56:21,760
You can make 'em round.

1368
01:56:21,794 --> 01:56:23,582
It's not a right-angle
kind of life.

1369
01:56:23,617 --> 01:56:24,992
Yeah.

1370
01:56:26,913 --> 01:56:29,302
Have room for your kids.

1371
01:56:31,873 --> 01:56:33,302
Yeah.

1372
01:56:36,512 --> 01:56:38,651
Hell, we could have
kids of our own.

1373
01:56:41,568 --> 01:56:43,478
We love each other.

1374
01:56:49,952 --> 01:56:51,708
Why not?

1375
01:56:56,832 --> 01:56:59,035
They wouldn't...

1376
01:56:59,071 --> 01:57:01,439
They wouldn't come out right.

1377
01:57:01,472 --> 01:57:03,838
Hell, I didn't come out right.

1378
01:57:03,871 --> 01:57:05,781
You came out OK.

1379
01:57:18,206 --> 01:57:20,116
What is it?

1380
01:57:21,567 --> 01:57:23,476
Come on.

1381
01:57:24,447 --> 01:57:27,960
Come on. I don't care.

1382
01:57:29,406 --> 01:57:30,835
I know.

1383
01:57:33,694 --> 01:57:35,353
You aren't going
to contaminate me...

1384
01:57:35,389 --> 01:57:38,074
any more than
I've already been.

1385
01:57:56,797 --> 01:57:59,546
I'm sorry.
I forgot to turn off the alarm.

1386
01:58:02,365 --> 01:58:04,665
I thought you weren't going in.

1387
01:58:04,700 --> 01:58:08,278
Well... I have to.

1388
01:58:10,460 --> 01:58:12,347
Call in sick.

1389
01:58:12,379 --> 01:58:14,268
No, I really do.

1390
01:58:14,300 --> 01:58:17,333
I really mean
you ought to call in sick.

1391
01:58:17,371 --> 01:58:19,476
Think they'll let you work?

1392
01:58:19,515 --> 01:58:20,978
There's something I got to get.

1393
01:58:21,020 --> 01:58:23,866
At the plant?
Are you wearing my shirt?

1394
01:58:23,899 --> 01:58:25,460
- Huh?
- My shirt!

1395
01:58:25,499 --> 01:58:28,848
You don't have to get up now.

1396
01:58:28,891 --> 01:58:32,022
Sweetheart, don't go try get
anything out of the plant.

1397
01:58:32,059 --> 01:58:33,783
If I get hung up
at the union meeting...

1398
01:58:33,819 --> 01:58:35,510
will you pick up
Paul Stone and the guy...

1399
01:58:35,546 --> 01:58:37,139
from the "New York Times"
at the airport?

1400
01:58:37,179 --> 01:58:38,739
Fuck no.

1401
01:58:38,779 --> 01:58:40,186
Come on, darling.

1402
01:58:40,219 --> 01:58:41,625
I don't know how late
this meeting will go tonight.

1403
01:58:41,659 --> 01:58:42,968
I don't want you doing that.

1404
01:58:43,002 --> 01:58:46,264
Well... I'm doing it.

1405
01:58:46,299 --> 01:58:48,665
You don't owe
the union anything.

1406
01:58:48,697 --> 01:58:50,520
Let's not fight.

1407
01:58:50,554 --> 01:58:53,041
You don't owe
the "New York Times" anything.

1408
01:58:53,081 --> 01:58:55,830
Let's not have a fight now.

1409
01:59:04,057 --> 01:59:05,967
We always can have a fight later.

1410
01:59:33,976 --> 01:59:39,759
Amazing grace

1411
01:59:39,800 --> 01:59:45,681
How sweet the sound

1412
01:59:45,720 --> 01:59:50,388
That saved a wretch...

1413
01:59:50,422 --> 01:59:54,219
- Give me your notes.
- OK.

1414
01:59:54,262 --> 01:59:56,237
Listen, you sure you're OK?

1415
01:59:56,279 --> 01:59:57,556
I'm OK.

1416
01:59:57,591 --> 01:59:58,900
- Bye-bye!
- Bye.

1417
01:59:58,935 --> 02:00:02,098
Once was lost

1418
02:00:02,134 --> 02:00:07,699
But now I'm found

1419
02:00:07,734 --> 02:00:10,549
Was blind

1420
02:00:10,582 --> 02:00:18,034
But now I see

1421
02:00:19,541 --> 02:00:24,909
'Twas grace that taught

1422
02:00:24,949 --> 02:00:30,099
My heart to fear

1423
02:00:30,133 --> 02:00:39,921
And grace my fears released

1424
02:00:39,957 --> 02:00:50,321
How precious
did that grace appear

1425
02:00:50,356 --> 02:01:00,426
The hour I first believed

1426
02:01:00,467 --> 02:01:10,025
Through many dangers,
toils, and snares

1427
02:01:10,067 --> 02:01:20,269
We have already come

1428
02:01:20,306 --> 02:01:30,671
'Twas grace that brought us
safe thus far

1429
02:01:30,707 --> 02:01:39,718
And grace will lead us home

1430
02:01:39,760 --> 02:01:49,614
When we've been there
ten thousand years

1431
02:01:49,650 --> 02:01:59,622
Bright-shining as the sun

1432
02:01:59,664 --> 02:02:04,999
We've no less days

1433
02:02:05,040 --> 02:02:10,222
To sing God's praise

1434
02:02:10,256 --> 02:02:20,108
As when we first begun

1435
02:02:20,143 --> 02:02:24,900
Amazing grace

1436
02:02:24,943 --> 02:02:30,310
How sweet the sound

1437
02:02:30,351 --> 02:02:40,171
That saved a wretch like me

1438
02:02:40,206 --> 02:02:44,810
I once was lost

1439
02:02:44,845 --> 02:02:49,931
But now I'm found

1440
02:02:49,966 --> 02:02:56,643
Was bound, but now I'm free

